[2026-04-22 api+frontend] Branch: =feature/resume-ingest-quality=.

Ingest pipeline:
- System prompt added to =ai/... ingest_resume.IngestResume=: preserve
  source order, strict =YYYY-MM= / =YYYY= / =present= dates, bullets
  stay with preceding experience, treat =--- PAGE BREAK ---= markers as
  invisible.
- Date parser (=_canonicalize_date_string= + =_split_date_range=) accepts
  =Jan 2020=, =January 2020=, =01/2020=, =2018 – 2020=, ranges, etc.
  Pydantic validators on Experience/Education/Project/Certification
  normalize before =parse_date=.
- =ResumeExperience.order= / =ExperienceDescription.order= / =ResumeProject.order= /
  =ProjectDescription.order= now populated during ingest
  (=create()= instead of =get_or_create()= — stops cross-resume
  Description reuse that was swapping bullets between users).
- =ResumeSerializer.get_related= now preserves join-table order on the
  wire (experiences + projects). Was dropping order because
  =Experience.objects.filter(pk__in=...)= re-sorted by PK.
- =extract_text_from_pdf= uses =pdfplumber= (layout-aware) with =pypdf=
  fallback; pages joined with =--- PAGE BREAK ---= markers.
- Added =pdfplumber>=0.11.0= to =api/pyproject.toml=.
- 27 =test_parse_date.py= + 3 =test_ingest_ordering.py= tests pass.

Frontend resume editor:
- Experience editor: disabled company input replaced with
  =<Companies::SelectOrCreate>= (now self-fetches companies; accepts
  =@selected=/=@onSelect=).
- =addDescription= saves a new experience first so the description can
  link by id; =Description= model gained =@belongsTo('experience')= and
  =@attr('number') order= for create payloads.
- Experience rows + description rows now have stacked ↑/↓ buttons for
  reorder. Posts to new bulk endpoints
  (=POST /resumes/:id/reorder-experiences/=,
   =POST /experiences/:id/reorder-descriptions/=), atomic per drag.
- =ember-animated= adopted for the reorder animation (~220ms move,
  easeOut). =liquid-fire= deprecation queued below.
- Chronology warning badge on any experience whose =startDate= inverts
  against its neighbor.

Dropped (explored and reverted):
- HTML5 drag-drop with a =<SortableList>= abstraction — event bubbling
  + textarea mousedown + row-height-vs-indicator issues made it brittle.
  Up/down buttons with keyed animated reorder are cleaner and
  keyboard-friendly.

